    <h1>Nofollow</h1>
    <p class="description">An HTML link attribute (<code>rel="nofollow"</code>) that instructs search engines not to pass link equity to the destination page. Originally a strict directive, Google now treats it as a <strong>ranking hint</strong> since 2019.</p>
    <div class="post-meta">
      <div class="meta-author">
        <div class="meta-avatar">AVR</div>
        <div class="meta-author-info">
          <span class="meta-author-name"><a href="/authors/akshay-vr/">Akshay VR</a></span>
